Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{0.5%tsp}. Once boiling, add the @rigatoni pasta{200%g} and cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

While the pasta is cooking, peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Chop the @Tenderstem Broccoli{150%g} into 3 pieces widthways. When the pasta has been cooking for ~{8%minutes}, add the tenderstem to the pasta and water and bring back to the boil. Cook with the pasta for the last ~{4%minutes} of cooking time.

When the pasta and broccoli are cooked, drain them in a #colander{}. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle} to stop them sticking together, leave the colander in the sink.

Pop your saucepan back on medium high heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}. Add the @sliced mushrooms{150%g} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir-fry until golden, ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Reduce the heat slightly then add the @creme fraiche{150%g} and @vegetable stock powder{1%tsp}. Pour in the @water{50%ml} for the sauce, bring to the boil and simmer for ~{2%minutes}. Remove from the heat. Stir in the @Truffle Zest{1%tsp} and @hard Italian Style Cheese{40%g}(grated).

Add the pasta and broccoli to the sauce and toss together. Taste and add salt and pepper if you feel it needs it. Serve in #bowls{}, sprinkle over the @walnuts{20} and enjoy!

> This decadent dinner takes only about 20 minutes to whip up - a perfect indulgent creamy and garlicky sauce balanced with bitter greens for the perfect pasta dish.